      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 186: `apply_ordered` accepts JSON payloads with extra entries because it only errors when there are more empty messages than entries. If the `.ts` file changed by removing or completing trailing untranslated messages after export, stale JSON can still be accepted silently, contradicting the documented guarantee that imports refuse changed files. Validate the entry count against the current untranslated message count before patching. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\n    current \u003d parse_untranslated(ts_path)\n    if len(entries) !\u003d len(current):\n        raise ValueError(\n            \u0027{}: expected {} entries but found {} empty messages; re-export \u0027\n            \u0027after running update-translations.py\u0027.format(\n                ts_path, len(entries), len(current)))\n\n    def resolver(index, ctx, src):\n```",
