      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 45: The fallback loop only handles missing executables. If `lupdate` exists but fails because it is the wrong Qt version or lacks required QML support, `subprocess.check_call` raises `CalledProcessError` and the script exits without trying the remaining candidates, which regresses the previous fallback behavior. Catch `subprocess.CalledProcessError` as a failed candidate and continue, preserving the last error for the final message. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\n    last_error \u003d None\n    for tool in LUPDATE_TOOLS:\n        try:\n            subprocess.check_call([tool] + base_args)\n            return\n        except FileNotFoundError:\n            continue\n        except subprocess.CalledProcessError as err:\n            last_error \u003d err\n            continue\n    raise RuntimeError(\n        \u0027No suitable lupdate tool completed successfully (tried: {}). \u0027\n        \u0027Install Qt Linguist tools or add lupdate to PATH.\u0027.format(\n            \u0027, \u0027.join(LUPDATE_TOOLS)))\n```",
